BUG-015 regression test: integration-results.json schema_version not validated

Test: Create integration-results.json with schema_version "0.9" and run quality_gate.sh
Expected: FAIL — schema_version "0.9" is not "1.1"
Actual: PASS — gate only checks key existence, not value

Verification:
  $ cat integration-results.json | grep schema_version
  "schema_version":"0.9"

  $ bash quality_gate.sh <tmpdir> 2>&1 | grep -i "schema_version.*integration"
  (no output — schema_version value is never checked for integration-results.json)

  $ bash quality_gate.sh <tmpdir> 2>&1 | grep "has 'schema_version'"
    PASS: has 'schema_version'

  (Key presence passes; value "0.9" is not validated)

Gate exit code: 0 (PASS despite non-conformant schema_version)

Comparison with tdd-results.json:
  quality_gate.sh line 222: [ "$sv" = "1.1" ] && pass "schema_version is '1.1'" || fail "..."
  quality_gate.sh line 371: json_has_key "$ij" "$key" && pass "has '${key}'" || fail "..."

  tdd-results.json checks VALUE ("1.1"); integration-results.json checks only KEY EXISTENCE.

Red phase: CONFIRMED — regression test demonstrates the bug
